An ambulance was sent to an address in the Balsall Heath area after a 999 call was made to West Midlands Ambulance Service at 3.45pm on New Year's Day.

Young Santino - a Czech national - died at Birmingham Children's Hospital after suffering extensive injuries and fractures to several parts of his body, West Midlands Police said.

The pair appeared at Birmingham Magistrates' Court with a translator yesterday for a short hearing.

Wearing blue T-shirts, they spoke only to confirm their names, ages and addresses.

The pair were remanded in custody to appear at Birmingham Crown Court tomorrow.

District Judge Rebecca Crane told them: 'This matter will now go to Birmingham Crown Court.

'You will appear on January 8. You are remanded in custody until that date.'

